pokedexEntries.gold: It is actually timid and easily spooked. If attacked, it flails about to fend off its attacker.
pokedexEntries.silver: Because its fangs are too heavy, it always keeps its head tilted down. However, its Bite is powerful.
pokedexEntries.crystal: It can make most any Pokémon run away simply by opening its mouth wide to reveal its big fangs.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Granbull has a particularly well- developed lower jaw. The enormous fangs are heavy, causing the Pokémon to tip its head back for balance. Unless it is startled, it will not try to bite indiscriminately.

pokedexEntries.emerald: It has a particularly well-developed lower jaw. The huge fangs are heavy, causing it to tilt its head. Unless it is startled, it will not try to bite.

pokedexEntries.sun: Its well-developed lower jaw and heavy fangs are its weapons. As long as it's not provoked, it rarely bites.
pokedexEntries.moon: More timid than Snubbull, this Pokémon is doted on by young people amused at the contrast between its looks and its attitude.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: While it has powerful jaws, it doesn’t care for disputes, so it rarely has a chance to display their might.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: Although it’s popular with young people, Granbull is timid and sensitive, so it’s totally incompetent as a watchdog.
